\section{Question 2B}

The NLTK book \href{http://www.nltk.org/book/ch05.html}{provides} a toy example of
regular expressions to tag parts of speech:
<<nltk_example>>=
patterns = [
	(r'.*ing$',               'VBG'),
	(r'.*ed$',                'VBD'),
	(r'.*.s$',                'VBZ'),
	(r'.*ould$',               'MD'),
	(r'.*\'s$',               'NN$'),
	(r'.*s$',                 'NNS'),
	(r'^-?[0-9]+(.[0-9]+)?$',  'CD'),
	(r'.*',                    'NN')
    ]
@

There are some issues in the example.

